when do you start decorating for fall autumn and christmas i absolutely love the fall season and i start putting out my fall garlands pumpkins and apple cider candles around the last week of august first week of september also christmas is my favorite holiday and i start decorating the house in the first week of november i am curious to know when others begin decorating and if anyone else loves that time of year as much as i do for fall i always decorate the beginning of september but for halloween i decorate the st of october and after halloween i put all the ghouls and skeletons away and prepare for turkey day for christmas i start decorating the weekend after thanksgiving and take the christmas decor down on new years day hope this helps Liturgical year Thanksgiving Autumn Christmas Japanese calendar National Football League Christmas tree Irish calendar Dean Koontz Kigo The Nightmare Before Christmas The Den (television) Easter Day of the Dead Holidays of the United States Christmas Eve Domesticated turkey Cuisine of Denmark Diwali Santa Claus USS Taylor (DD-468) The Beatles discography USS Alamo USS Taussig (DD-746) USS America (CV-66) Judy Garland Daylight saving time Port Authority Trans-Hudson Saturday Night Live Birthday Holidays in Canada USS Stockham (DD-683) RuneScape economy Beauty and the Beast: The Enchanted Christmas Cliff Richard Christmas worldwide Advent Academic term USS Willard Keith (DD-775) Spice Girls Garfield Candle The Star Wars Holiday Special Roman calendar Bank Holiday Billboard Hot 100 The Adventures of Pete & Pete USS Wallace L. Lind (DD-703) Bon Jovi Clay Aiken Christianization Pumpkin Walt Disney World College Program Pysanka Hebrew calendar Carnival USS Aspro (SSN-648) USS Ault (DD-698) KROQ Acoustic Christmas Rent (film) Holiday World & Splashin' Safari USS Wisconsin (BB-64) USS Abbot (DD-629) Season Chicago (band) Thursday USS Vermont (BB-20) The Smashing Pumpkins USS Waters (DD-115) USS Missouri (BB-63) Six Flags Over Texas My Pa